# Vidsembly Free Tools Platform

This repo powers **tools.vidsembly.com**. Treat it as a scalable free-tool platform, not a collection of one-off pages.

## Tool Architecture

- Register every tool in `src/lib/tools/tool-data.ts` before building a page.
- Tool pages must use shared components — never hand-roll SEO, FAQ, CTA, or related-tool sections.
- Use `ToolPage` as the page template; pass only the tool-specific converter UI as `children`.

### Adding a new tool

1. Add a `ToolConfig` entry to `toolConfigs` in `tool-data.ts` (SEO, FAQs, info sections, related tools, trust points).
2. Build the converter as a client component under `components/tools/`.
3. Create `app/tools/[slug]/page.tsx`:

```tsx
import { ToolPage } from "@/components/tools/ToolPage";
import { MyToolConverter } from "@/components/tools/MyToolConverter";
import { generateToolMetadata } from "@/lib/tools/seo";
import { getRequiredToolConfig } from "@/lib/tools/get-required-tool-config";

const tool = getRequiredToolConfig("my-tool-slug");
export const metadata = generateToolMetadata(tool);

export default function MyToolPage() {
  return (
    <ToolPage tool={tool}>
      <MyToolConverter trustPoints={tool.trustPoints} />
    </ToolPage>
  );
}
```

### Automatic per-tool features (via `ToolPage` + `ToolSeoContent`)

- SEO, Open Graph, and Twitter metadata (`generateToolMetadata`)
- FAQ section (`ToolFaq`)
- Informational content (`ToolInfoSections`)
- Related tools (`RelatedTools`)
- Vidsembly CTA (`VidsemblyCta`)
- JSON-LD structured data (`ToolJsonLd` — SoftwareApplication + FAQPage)

## Design Rules

- Keep the existing dark Vidsembly design system (`globals.css` tokens, Jost font, blue/purple accents).
- Reuse existing components (`ToolPageLayout`, `FileDropzone`, `ToolTrustBox`, `ToolCard`, etc.).
- Do not redesign existing pages unless explicitly requested.
- Do not introduce new color schemes, popups, banners, or overlays.

## Code Rules

- Prefer reusable components over page-specific logic.
- Put conversion/helper logic in `lib/tools/[category]/` (e.g. `lib/tools/audio/`).
- Avoid duplicating FAQ, SEO, CTA, or related-tool logic across pages.
- Mark tools as `available: true` in `tool-data.ts` to enable homepage links.
